ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Let us review the history of this farm: [1] "Late April" (2006) this
farm was placed under a swine quarantine order; [2] Around the 12th
July 2006 the owner & his son were arrested on a 19-count indictment
for operating a slaughterhouse without a license, resulting from
raids on the farm in March & April 2006; [3] Between April & July
2006, 5 pigs in relation to this farm have been diagnosed with
trichinosis; [4] At some point the Maryland Department of Agriculture
scheduled to test the pigs on this farm on 14 Sep 2006, a date some 5
months after the investigation started. By then [5] the pigs had
disappeared. No comment. Res ipso loquitor. MHJ Mod]
